The Davidoff Escurio Petit Robusto is a luxurious cigar that follows the high-quality reputation of one of the most well-known and respected brands in the market today. Tobaccos from Nicaragua, San Andres, Ecuador and the Dominican Republic perfectly harmonize to create an intensely flavorful medium to full-bodied blend. Smokers are treated to warm notes of dark cocoa, aged oak and gentle spices for an exceptionally diverse flavor profile.
Now available in a 5 pack, this is a fantastic example in which you get what you pay for. Receiving an outstanding 92 rating from Cigar Journal, this smoke is for Cigar Aficionados who demand high-quality, full flavor and pure luxury!

title: La Flor Dominicana Double Ligero The Chisel Maduro
description:
Size: 6 X 54
Box Count: 10
Wrapper: Ecuadorian Sumatra
Binder: Dominican Republic
Filler: Dominican Republic
The La Flor Dominicana The Chisel Maduro is a full-bodied, meticulously constructed luxury cigar. Following their trend in big and bold, they chose a dark, oily Ecuadorian Sumatra wrapper and Dominican binder and long-fillers. Incase you weren’t aware, the term Ligero refers to the top priming of leaves on a tobacco plant. These leaves receive the maximum amount of sunlight and are much bolder and spicier in flavor than a typical leaf. Litto Gomez, the creator of this term, decided to DOUBLE the amount of Ligero in this blend.

Size: 4 1/2 x 60

Fans of full body cigars will love the finely aged San Andres maduro wrapper, rich Corojo Maduro binder and a mix of fillers from Honduras, Brazil and the Dominican Republic.

The Olmec Claro Robusto is a Fox favorite – get this cigar in your smoking rotation today!

This is stronger and spicier than the regular production “Brown Label” line of cigars and the use of the Broadleaf adds a hint of sweetness in the complexity. Not technically limited production, this cigar is released in small batches – so jump on it when it’s available!

The results make a delicious full bodied blend with hints of cedar, spice and earthiness that finishes with a natural sweetness.
These will quickly become a fan favorite and production will be limited – jump on it now!

Size: 4 3/4 x 60

This medium to full-bodied cigar will deliver notes of dark roast coffee, aged cedar and earthy spices for a smooth finish. Jump on this blend now – every release is done in limited batches.

Enjoy this premium cigar when you are looking for a medium-bodied smoke from your friends at Fox Cigar.

Once the wrapper is fully cured, it holds together a San Andres Mexican binder and a mix of Honduran / Nicaraguan fillers. Add this to your rotation NOW before it’s gone!

It is wrapped in a golden Connecticut shade leaf with a binder that consists of a special blend of ancient Mata Fina tobacco.
The Highclere Castle Edwardian filler is something super duper cool. Nick Melillo, owner and master blender of Foundation, states that the some of the filler leaves come from their hybrid-seed called the Nicadan. This adds a generous amount of flavor and strength to it that’s unique to this line of cigars. Hints of spice, dried fruit and a subtle smokiness can all be noted.

description:
Size: Mixed

Wrapper: Maduro
Binder: Nicaragua
Filler: Nicaragua
Drew Estate has been running the game for years now – producing nothing but premium cigars that are just bursting with flavor! The Deadwoods are absolutely to die for (and have a funny story to go with them).
From the DE Website: “Sweet Jane was born in a brothel and is known for breaking hearts and bringing the strongest of men to their knees. Fat Bottom Betty is Sweet Jane’s sister that is fresh out of rehab and back out their spreading the love with her ‘fat bottom’.“
The Leather Rose is supposedly the baddest of the bunch (robbing banks, you know – the usual). Last but not least is Crazy Alice, the firecracker of the group who Drew Estate claims is a “pistol cracking hussy”… we’re just going to go with it.
Unusual – but are we really going to question anything that Drew Estate does? Didn’t think so.
In this tasting kit you will receive the following cigars:

(1) Sweet Jane
(1) Crazy Alice
(1) Leather Rose Torpedo
(1) Fat Bottom Betty Toro
(1) Fat Bottom Betty Gordito

The Montesino Toro Natural cigar is proudly produced at the famous Tabacalera A. Fuente and has become a popular premium selection for many Cigar Aficionados. Handmade utilizing a smooth Connecticut Shade wrapper, premium Dominican long-fillers and vintage Nicaraguan binders; this is what you need in your smoking rotation.
The unique five-year aged blend is from a selection of mellow to mild Dominican tobaccos that treats smokers to warm hints of sweet cedar, earthy tones and delicate spices with a creamy nutty twist thanks to the natural shade wrapper. Montesino possesses the same high-quality and excellent consistency that Arturo Fuente cigars are known for. Fuente cigars truly made a bargain humidor essential at this price.

The Zino Nicaragua utilizes a beautiful golden brown Ecuadorian Connecticut wrapper with a classic Nicaraguan binder and perfectly aged tobaccos from Nicaragua, Honduras and the Dominican Republic. Smokers are treated to a medium-bodied cigar with warm notes of dark chocolate, roasted coffee, and aged cedarwood for a creamy finish. When looking to smoke quality, smoke Davidoff – trust your friends at Fox Cigar.

The Panetela size with a classic pigtail top is truly a treat for your palate.
Davidoff’s portfolio of cigars is considered to be some of the most luxurious cigars you can get your hands on, don’t think about it twice.

The Padron 1926 Serie Maduro Sampler is a beautiful selection of some the best Padron has to offer. They have always been known for their high-quality, delicious cigars and the 1926 line is an elegant representation of it. It was crafted in honor of Jose Padron’s 75th birthday. These cigars are curated with the best Nicaraguan tobaccos that are aged for 5-10 years! Each one is wrapped in a rich Nicaraguan leaf.
Full-bodied and full of flavor, these cigars have notes of coffee and gentle spices that blend ever so perfectly. So go ahead and treat yourself with this Padron sampler and enjoy a true luxury smoking experience.

Basically, you need to smoke this and get it in your humidor ASAP.

Binder: San Andres
Filler: Honduran
The Baccarat Rothschild cigar is mild and sweet everyday smoke – perfect for any occasion and curated for cigar aficionado’s who prefer a mellow, smoother smoke.
This cigar uses perfectly aged Havana-seed Honduran long-fillers and an authentic San Andres Mexican binder held together with a golden-brown Connecticut shade wrapper. Smokers are treated to crisp notes of freshly dark roasted coffee, sweet cocoa and hints of cedar for a creamy finish. The price on these delicious cigars is hard to pass up – pick some up today while you can!

This full-bodied cigar brings a very rich, complex smoking profile that features hints of cocoa, nut, coffee and leather. It finishes with just the right amount of bold spice and a hint of sweetness that is oh-so-smooth! Add the L-500 Oscuro to your smoking rotation when you want something to pair with a great dinner!

Davidoff Special T cigars are a part of the Aniversario series, referred to as one of the best-selling lines Davidoff has produced – and for good reason. The Davidoff Special T utilizes a unique Torpedo shape that allows for a more personal preference cut.
The Davidoff Aniversario Special T is an elegant blend of a complex yet extremely smooth profile. Smokers are treated to a medium-bodied smoke with warm hints of toasted almonds, earthy spices and smokey cedar for a peppery finish. Now available in a 4 pack, this is a fantastic example in which you get what you pay for.

title: Punch After Dinner
description:
Size: 7 1/4 x 45
Box Count: 25
Wrapper: Ecuador Sumatra
Binder: Honduras
Filler: Honduras
Punch is proudly handmade in Honduras and features an eclectic 3 county blend (Dominican, Honduran, and Nicaraguan) of long fillers. It is then carefully wrapped in an Ecuadorian Sumatra wrapper. The wrapper adds an earthy profile with a heavy peppery spice. This staple cigar is perfect for your late night smokes!

title: Jaime Garcia Reserva Especial Toro Gordo
description:
Size: 6 x 60
Box Count: 20
Wrapper: Connecticut Broadleaf
Binder: Nicaragua
Filler: Nicaragua
The Jaime Garcia Reserva Especial Toro Gordo features only the finest aged Nicaraguan tobaccos complemented by a beautifully dark Connecticut Broadleaf wrapper. This full-bodied complex cigar features creamy notes of coffee, cocoa, spice, and leather. These cigars are made with the ultimate precision, Jaime Garcia himself studied the art of cigar making from his brilliant father, Jose ‘Pepin’ Garcia. They are a great value and definitely deserve a spot in your humidor.

description:

Wrapper: Dominican
Binder: Dominican
Filler: Dominican
Fuente Fuente OpusX The Lost City is one of the most exclusive and extraordinary cigars ever created. As one of the largest cigars in the Lost City collection, the Toro has the coolest smoke and possibly the mellowest taste. It has a slight sweetness like that of a subtly sugared Latin American pastry. Very light hints of black pepper are juxtaposed against the softer flavor notes to deliver a fascinating blend of tastes throughout the long burn time.

Mild to medium in body, this one delivers a great floral and aromatic smoke, with a little bit of spice. The Acid C Notes come in 5 packs or boxes of 100.

description:

Binder: Dominican
Filler: Dominican

You should definitely add the 1875 Bully to your smoking rotation. Pro Tip: This is one of our favorite cigars to pair with coffee in the morning.

Size: 5 1/4 x 42

Wrapper: Cameroon
Binder: Connecticut Broadleaf
Filler: Dominican Republic
The CAO Flavours Cherrybomb Corona cigar is composed of a unique and aromatic blend. These cigars are absolutely scrumptious – furnishing a velvety Cameroon leaf wrapper and aged Dominican tobaccos for the binder and filler. Pops of cherry, black pepper and a mild creamy vanilla can all be noted. This is a great smoke for any occasion – and it’s easy on the wallet.

Size: 5 x 42
Box Count: 24
Wrapper: Connecticut Broadleaf
Binder: Nicaragua
Filler: Nicaragua
Rocky Patel Java Maduro is a coffee-infused cigar that is handmade by Drew Estate exclusively for Rocky Patel. This cigar has a blend of all-Nicaraguan fillers draped in a delicious dark, Connecticut Broadleaf wrapper. It is then infused with coffee and mocha. Dark chocolate, espresso and rich notes of earth are tasted throughout the smoke. This is for you coffee lovers!

title: Java Latte Corona

Binder: Nicaragua
Filler: Nicaragua
Rocky Patel Java Latte is a coffee-infused Cigar manufactured at Drew Estate exclusively for Rocky Patel. The Java Latte is a luscious blend that provides flavors of sweet cream, mocha, and a buttery finish with, of course, hints of coffee. If you are looked for a quality dessert cigar, this is just for you!

The Montecristo 1935 Anniversary Nicaragua Churchill cigars were created to celebrate the 85th anniversary of the Montecristo brand. This delicious cigar is a Nicaraguan puro that was created by master blender AJ Fernandez using the best tobacco from his farms.
This cigar is rich, complex and one of the best Montecristo’s that has hit the market (well if you like great spice, chocolate notes and a smooth creamy finish).

If you love the M line and you’re a big fan of espresso (who isn’t?) then check out the next evolution of the M line of cigars today.

description:
Size: 7 X 40
Box Count: 24
Wrapper: Connecticut Havana Seed
Binder: Mexican San Andres

Nicholas Melillo is back at it again with the second release to the Tabernacle. This time it is blended with Connecticut U.S.A grown Habano seed (aka Havana Seed CT #142)  and aged / fermented an additional 3 years in Nicaragua. Once the wrapper is fully cured, it holds together a San Andres Mexican binder and a mix of Honduran / Nicaraguan fillers. Add this to your rotation NOW.

description:
Size: 4 1/2 X 50
Box Count: 20
Wrapper: Ecuador Habano
Binder: Nicaragua
Filler: Nicaragua
The Flor De Las Antillas Maduro Petite Robusto translates to “Flower of The Antilles” and this is My Father’s tribute to Cuba. This wonderfully crafted cigar is blended from only the finest Nicaraguan tobacco and enclosed by a lustrous Ecuador Habano Maduro wrapper. Said to be medium to full-bodied, it invites a combo of cedar and spice with a great overall creamy flavor. This impeccable cigar deserves a place in your humidor. Order a box from Fox Cigar today!

title: M By Macanudo Coffee Toro
description:
Size: 6 x 50
Box Count: 20
Wrapper: Indonesian
Binder: Philippine
Filler: Nicaraguan
The M by Macanudo Coffee Toro is a full-flavor smoke that happens to be the first infused cigar released by Macanudo. Featuring a savory Indonesian wrapper, aged Nicaraguan tobaccos for the binder and for the filler. Dark espresso, sweet cedar and white pepper all coalesce to create a creamy, medium-bodied smoke.

title: Aganorsa La Validacion Habano Gran Robusto
Padron Damaso No. 34 Red Label
description:
Size: 6 x 52
Box Count: 20
Wrapper: Ecuadorian Connecticut
Binder: Nicaraguan
Filler: Nicaraguan
The Padron Damaso No. 34 Red Label was produced in honor of Damaso Padron, a founding father of Padron cigars who has set the market standard in premium cigar making. This cigar was curated for those in search of the high-quality and excellent consistency from Padron but in a more mild profile. The Damaso Red Label offers a more robust flavor profile.
Hand-crafted with a luxurious Connecticut-seed wrapper, the blend utilizes the finest aged Nicaraguan tobaccos for the binder and filler. This is a mild to medium-bodied cigar, with warm notes of fresh cocoa, sweet caramel and smoked cedar. The burn and draw are exceptionally smooth with hints of subtle spices for a toasty finish. Padron’s Damaso series is a blend crafted for over five generations – this is a cigar worthy of its 91 rating from Cigar Aficionado.

title: Liga Privada T52 Flying Pig
description:
Size: 4 x 60
Box Count: 12
Wrapper: Sungrown
Binder: Nicaragua
Filler: Nicaragua
The Liga T52 Flying Pig by Drew Estate is a uniquely crafted cigar. It contains a stalk-cut wrapper. This means it is cut and hung in an exclusive aging barn while still on the stalk. After aging, it is then complimented with a Brazilian binder and Nicaraguan/Honduran blend. All this calls for a wonderfully spicy cigar with coffee, cocoa, nuts and spice flavors. It is medium bodied and a great smoke for any occasion! Get one today for yourself.

title: La Flor Dominicana La Nox
description:
Size: 6 1/2 X 50
Box Count: 20
Wrapper: Brazilian
Binder: San Andres
Filler: Dominican
The La Flor Dominicana La Nox (latin for night) uses a dark Cuban-seed Brazilian maduro wrapper, Mexican San Andres binder and a Dominican filler that comes from the LFD’s Estancia La Flor de Palma farm. This medium to full bodied cigar has a very bold, rich flavor profile that’s extremely exciting to smoke. The La Nox is a limited production cigar from the company – so get your hands on some while you can!

description:
Size: 5 1/2 x 50

Binder: Nicaraguan
Filler: Nicaraguan

Having earned countless 90 + cigar ratings, this new line of cigars is no different from his collection of premium boutique smokes. The Sixty cigar blend utilizes a vintage Mexican San Andres wrapper covering a never before used selection of perfectly aged Nicaraguan binder and long-fillers. Each batch of long-filler tobaccos is aged for no less than 6 years before being hand-rolled with an additional 2 years of aging to cement the quality and flavor. Smokers are treated to a medium to full-bodied profile ranging with strong hints of freshly roasted dark coffee, aged oak, and subtle earthy spices for a toasty finish. Binder: Nicaraguan
Filler: Nicaraguan
The Joya de Nicaragua Joya Black Toro cigar is the highly anticipated follow-up to the Joya Red blend – the first blend in the line up to incorporate a dark San Andres Negro wrapper. This cigar is handcrafted to perfection with finely aged Nicaraguan fillers from the regions of Esteli, Condega and Jalapa to truly bring the Nicaraguan flavor bomb that Joya cigars are known for.
Factory Manager, Mario Perez, went on to say “We wanted to create a blend with a rich Nicaraguan tobacco yet without the overpowering strength” and that is exactly what these cigars are – well constructed and evenly balanced. Smokers are presented to a medium to full-bodied profile with hints of dark cocoa, dark roast coffee and subtle peppery hints for a warm finish.

Two distinct blends, one by Johnson and one by the Garcias, are handmade in a 7.25 x 50 Double Corona called the Prominente Especial. Fratello Arlequin (1)
Fratello Sorella (1)
Fratello Bianco II (1)
Fratello Classico Toro (1)

The two newbies (Arlequin + Sorella) are both blended at Joya De Nicaragua factory in Nicaragua. The Atlequin features a Mexican wrapper with Ecuadorian binder and Nicaraguan + Peruvian fillers. While the Sorella uses an Ecuadorian habano wrapper overtop an Indonesian binder with Dominican + Nicaraguan fillers.
Fratello founder, Omar de Frias, says “These new blends will serve as market research for our company.”
So what are you waiting for? Give this sampler a try, it’s out of this world!

title: Arturo Fuente Hemingway House Humidor Package
description:
Size: 7 x 48
Cigar Count: 60
Wrapper: Unknown
Binder: Unknown
Filler: Unknown
The Arturo Fuente Hemingway House Humidor Package is extraordinarily unique! This limited edition humidor is designed to look just like the Hemingway House that sits at Chateau de la Fuente, the farm owned by Arturo Fuente in Caribe, Dominican Republic, that produces all of the tobacco used for the Fuente Fuente OpusX line. The home was built to replicate Ernest Hemingways historic house in Key West! It aims to replicate the home by including Spanish tile on the base of the humidor and gold inlays for the railings. The lid uses metal to replicate the look of stained glass, which is used throughout the building. The incredible artistry goes further with animals you’ll see throughout including a blue-eyed white horse. Each humidor is handmade in France. Elie Bleu has said “this is one of the most intensive humidors it’s ever made”. Holding up to 110 cigars and measures at 14.45 inches x 12.6 inches x 9.84 inches. This Rare humidor also has a built in hygrometer, made to use the 320g Boveda packs, which are stored inside of the magnetically attached cover.

description:

The Fratello Concealed Carry is a curated collection of 6 themed cigars, each with its own exclusive blend and story.  Each blend is meant to portray a period in history that some would like to forget and others remember.  This small batch of 1,000 cans with 12 cigars were offered at the 2024 PCA Trade show to only 75 select retailers to allow their customers to try these very limited blends from Fratello.
The first cigar in the series takes it’s inspiration from the 18th Amendment of the United States Constitution which established the prohibition of alcohol in the U.S.A. The result of decades of efforts by the temperance movement, which believed that poverty and other societal problems were caused by alcohol consumption, the 18th Amendment was ratified on January 16, 1919 and the ban of alcohol sales began. Luckily, the ban only lasted until 1933 when the 21st Amendment was ratified on December 5 of that year, repealing the 18th Amendment.

Production was limited to only 1000 boxes and the craftsmanship on these premium cigars is truly impressive. Now available in a 5 pack, this is a fantastic example in which you get what you pay for.
This elegant cigar is finished with a Cuban box-press design that noticeably delivers a longer and smoother smoke. Utilizing an authentic Enganoso wrapper over a Connecticut Broadleaf binder and a premium blend of Nicaraguan and Dominican tobaccos, this is a Crux cigar that does not lack complexity. Smokers are treated to a medium to full-bodied profile with bright hints of creamy espresso, aged cedar, dark cocoa and subtle hints of black pepper for a warm finish.

Covered in a dark Habano Jalapa wrapper, this Lancero sized cigar uses the finest Nicaraguan and Honduran tobaccos available for the binder and filler. Smokers are presented with warm notes of aged cedar and earthy tones with hints of freshly roasted coffee for a toasty finish. The unique flavor profile and top-quality construction make this cigar a great smoke from start to finish.
As one of the 5 original blends from Crux Cigars now available in a 5 pack, you won’t be disappointed with this premium cigar.

The Crux Epicure Robusto Extra is here and you definitely don’t want to miss out. This bad boy boasts a sweet-ass Connecticut Shade wrapper and a phenomenal blend of Nicaraguan tobaccos for the binder and filler. Hints of creamiliciousness are poppin’ in every puff.
So go ahead, dip your toe in the Crux water and test it yourself.

title: FFOX “Heaven and Earth” Tauros the Bull Natural Vintage 2020
description:
Size: 6 x 62
Box Count: 10
Wrapper: Dominican
Binder: Dominican
Filler: Dominican
The FFOX “Heaven and Earth” Tauros the Bull Natural is a celebration of the harmonious blend of flavors and aromas that only the finest tobacco leaves can provide. This exquisite cigar features a Dominican wrapper cultivated with utmost care to ensure a smooth and visually stunning appearance. Having flavors of Pepper, leather, cedar and coffee bean. The wrapper’s natural oils enhance the overall smoking experience, delivering a luscious and complex flavor profile. These cigars are from the 2020 release, have been aging in our humidor and are now available for purchase!

title: FFOX “Heaven and Earth” El Escorpion Natural Vintage 2022
description:
Size: 6 3/8 x 50
Box Count: 10
Wrapper: Dominican Chateau de la Fuente Sun Grown Rosado
Binder: Dominican Chateau de la Fuente Sun Grown Rosado
Filler: Dominican Chateau de la Fuente Sun Grown Rosado
The FFOX El Escorpion is a masterpiece and comes out only twice a year! This cigar is unlike any other cigar, very rare and highly sought after by both cigar aficionados and collectors. Once you light up Opus X El Escorpion, you’ll understand why it’s so special. The flavors are rich and complex with notes of cedar, oak, pepper spice and leather. This cigar is a true masterpiece crafted with attention to detail. If you are lucky enough to acquire one, take your time and enjoy the splendor of this rare gemstone. These cigars are from the 2022 release, have been aging in our humidor and are now available for purchase!

Treat yourself to one of the most rare and sought after cigars from the OpusX line. This beautifully crafted figurado starts off smooth with hints of leather and dried fruit. title: Kentucky Fire Cured Sweets Fat Molly
description:
Size: 5 x 56
Bundle Count: 10
Wrapper: Mexican San Andres
Binder: Nicaraguan
Filler: Nicaraguan
The Kentucky Fire Cured Sweets Fat Molly Bundle of cigars is one smoke that you will not forget. Using only fire-cured Nicaraguan filler tobaccos, you’re in for one zesty treat. A super aromatic and flavorful blend, the bold Mexican San Andres wrapper and the sweetened tip adds all the complexity you need.
Smokers are welcomed to a medium-bodied profile with warm hints of aged oak, sweet maple syrup and rich bourbon that will have you feeling like you’re relaxing by a fireside. Whether you are a cigar novice venturing off into the world of smoking or a cigar aficionado – these bad boys are a must-try smoking experience!

title: Epicure Maduro Toro Pack
description:
Size: 6 1/4 x 52
Sleeve Count: 4 Packs
Pack Count: 5
Wrapper: San Andres
Binder: Nicaraguan
Filler: Nicaraguan
The Crux Epicure Maduro Toro is a full-bodied cigar where timeless flavor collides with smoothness and boldness in every puff. Featuring a premium San Andres Maduro wrapper, smokers are accompanied by robust notes of peppery spices, sweet cinnamon and dark chocolate. A beautiful balance between flavor and strength that is perfect for any occasion.
From the elegant cigar construction to the complex flavor profile, the Crux Epicure is a must-have for your collection.
Remember: When you order a Sleeve you will receive 20 cigars total. When you order a Single Pack, you will receive 5 cigars.

title: Guild Corona
description:

Binder: Nicaraguan
Filler: Nicaraguan
The Crux Guild Corona is a full-bodied gem of a cigar that everyone should try. Featuring a scrumptious Ecuadorian wrapper and Nicaraguan tobaccos for the binder and filler. This cigar is perfect for any occasion – whether it’s staying home, chillin’ with the homies or going out for a night to party hardy.
